H1> About the banlist

P> The banlist blocks unwanted visitors at the door. You can ban by IP address, by email address, or by a wildcard pattern of either.

Q> What's this section for?
A> It allows you to ban visitors to your site, either by their IP address and/or email address. Banned addresses are checked very early in the request lifecycle so blocked visitors never reach your content.

Q> Why do I have to give a reason?
A> You don't strictly have to, but it is strongly recommended. The reason field is shown to other administrators so they can understand why the ban exists – without it, somebody might lift the ban by mistake.

TIP> Use the [b]Expiry[/b] field to schedule short-term bans (for example, 24 h cool-downs). Permanent bans should be reserved for repeat offenders.

WARN> Banning by IP affects every user behind that IP – including legitimate visitors on shared connections (universities, mobile carriers, NAT). Prefer email/account bans whenever possible.
